# Admin UI Patterns

## Architecture

- React SPA with React Router (`basename="/admin"`)
- Auth context (`useAuth`) provides `account`, `login`, `logout`, `refreshAccount`
- Refresh context (`useRefresh`) provides `refreshKey`, `triggerRefresh`
- API calls via `fetch` to `/api/...` (proxied by `serve.cjs` in production)

## Component Rules

1. All pages use `useRefresh()` and re-fetch data when `refreshKey` changes
2. Show `PageSkeleton` or `ListSkeleton` during loading — never blank screens
3. URLs displaying apps use `/{account.alias || account.id}/{slug}/`
4. Use CSS classes from `styles.css` — no inline styles for colors/spacing
5. Modals use `.modal-overlay` + `.modal-content` classes
6. Tabs use `.tabs` + `.tab` + `.tab-active` classes

## Page Structure

- `Dashboard.tsx` — stats overview, recent items
- `AppList.tsx` — list apps, create new
- `AppDetail.tsx` — tabbed (Configuration, Versions, Settings)
- `MFEList.tsx` — list MFEs (active/archived)
- `MFEDetail.tsx` — version history, metadata
- `Layouts.tsx` — available layout templates
- `Settings.tsx` — account alias, profile
- `Login.tsx` / `Register.tsx` — auth forms

## API Pattern

```tsx
const [data, setData] = useState(null);
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
const { refreshKey } = useRefresh();

useEffect(() => {
  setLoading(true);
  fetch("/api/endpoint", { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }})
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(d => setData(d.data))
    .finally(() => setLoading(false));
}, [refreshKey]);

if (loading) return <PageSkeleton />;
```
